# Python Style (3.13+)

## Type hints: use built-in generics

```python
# bad
from typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple
def f(items: List[str]) -> Optional[Dict[str, int]]: ...

# good
def f(items: list[str]) -> dict[str, int] | None: ...
```

## Deprecated APIs

- `datetime.utcnow()` -> `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` (deprecated since 3.12)

## File I/O

- Always `open(path, "r", encoding="utf-8")` -- never rely on platform default encoding

## Imports

- Module-level only; no `import pandas` inside a method body
- Exception: lazy imports behind `try/except ImportError` for optional deps (e.g. alpaca-py)

## No side effects at import time

```python
# bad -- creates directory when any module imports this package
LOGS_DIR = Path("logs")
LOGS_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)

# good -- defer to explicit setup call
def ensure_logs_dir() -> Path:
    d = Path("logs")
    d.mkdir(exist_ok=True)
    return d
```
